{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Hybrid — REST + SSE Notifications\n      REST for control plane (start workflow, report results, approve). SSE for notifications (state changes, approval requests, resume signals). Best of both worlds.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            REST for reliability — every state change is an explicit API call\n            SSE for speed — instant notifications, no polling delay\n            Graceful degradation: if SSE disconnects, backend can poll REST\n            Matches Cortex's existing architecture (REST + smart polling)\n            UI gets real-time updates via same SSE pattern\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Two communication channels to maintain\n            Must ensure REST and SSE stay consistent\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Flow: Backend calls REST to start workflow → Cortex evaluates DAG, returns next nodes → Backend executes, calls REST with result → if HITL: Cortex persists pause state (REST), fires SSE to UI + sends Telegram notification → user approves via REST endpoint → Cortex fires SSE \"resume\" to backend → backend calls REST to get next nodes\n        \n      \n      \n        ⭐ Recommended — aligns with Cortex's existing patterns and provides both reliability and real-time UX","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774372811264}
